&ldquo;Once in a blue moon an idea sweeps through the bridge world and revolutionises thinking. The so-called Law of Total Tricks is so accurate in assessing potential in the contested auction and so easy to use (meaning in the book) that it is being introduced early and used to justify many subsequent bidding decisions.&rdquo;
From the book &ldquo;Understanding the contested auction&rdquo; of Ron Klinger and Andrew Kambites.
